==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monkeys puzzle
<hw>Mon"key's puz"zle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A lofty
coniferous Chilian tree (<spn>Araucaria araucana</spn>, formerly
<spn>Araucaria imbricata</spn>), the branches of which are so crowded
and intertwisted ⟦ldquo⟧as to puzzle a monkey to climb.⟦rdquo⟧ It is
also called <altname>monkey puzzle</altname> and <altname>monkey puzzle
tree</altname>. The edible nuts are over an inch long, and are called
<xex>pi⟦ntil⟧on</xex> by the Chilians.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monkeytail</ent>⟦br⟧
